    "body": "Sure. I have various monkey patches on the GroupBy. I use a downsample monkey patched function that replicates the behavior for resample I'm requesting. So something like this works:\n\n``` python\nohlc_dict = {\n        'open':'first', \n        'high': 'max', \n        'low': 'min', \n        'close': 'last',\n        'vol': 'sum'\n        }\n\ndef ohlc_grouped_cython(grouped):\n    hldf = grouped.agg(ohlc_dict)\n    # set column order back\n    hldf = hldf.reindex(columns=['open', 'high', 'low', 'close', 'vol'])\n    return hldf\nDataFrameGroupBy.ohlc = ohlc_grouped_cython\n\nmonthly = df.downsample('MS').ohlc()\n```\n\nI also may want to send the GroupBy to multiple functions. While resampling is fast, it makes more sense to do the grouping once and pass it around. \n"
  },
